HEADWORD: Epileptogenous
<hw>Ep`i*lep*tog"e*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'epi`lhptos</grk> epileptic + <ets>-genous</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Producing epilepsy or epileptoid convulsions; --
applied to areas of the body or of the nervous system, stimulation of
which produces convulsions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epileptoid</ent>⟦br⟧
